The City of Cape Town and Sanparks have released the report on the fire. Sanparks believes it was started 'intentionally' . #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - There's no evidence at this point indicating that the raging fire that laid bare tracts of land on Table Mountain in April was a natural occurrence. The blaze decimated large parts of the University of Cape Town, causing widescale damage to historic buildings. READ: Cape Town fires | UCT assessing extent of damage The City of Cape Town and Sanparks have released the report on the fire. Sanparks believes the fire was started 'intentionally'. Watch the video above for more details on this story.